The paper focuses on developing a real-time integrated framework for multi-target object detection and tracking using 3D LIDAR in an urban scenario. This involves handling uncertainties arising from sensing limitations and complexity of target object movement. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category, as it deals with autonomous vehicles and their perception technology. Additionally, the paper also involves computer vision (cs.CV) techniques for object detection and tracking, and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for heuristics rule-based filtering and probabilistic tracking. The use of probabilistic tracking also suggests that the paper may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the integration of different components to achieve a specific goal, which suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
